	* lib.c: Lots of changes, including  - get_die_magic() Get
	DIE_MAGIC value from .magic.dat (or cerate if not found)

2000-11-14 09:27  miller

	* mail.c: Innumerous changes, some of which are:  - Add new command
	'promote'  - Resign command now needs email for master (and can
	resign observers)  - Added calls to shorthand functions for
	SHORTHAND press games  - set a player flag when a power resigns
	(for future use to tell resigned players game has ended.)
	
	 - Allow termination of unstarted games
	 - Restrict games witn F_NORESUME to master-only resumation
	 - Do not show password of player when doing a 'become' command

2000-11-14 09:27  miller

	* st_retreat.c: Allow wing units REcalcultate blockade settings
	Allow retreat moves syntax checking

2000-11-14 09:27  miller

	* st_movement.c: Added move syntax checker Allow wing units to be
	used Allow transformations REcalculate blockade settings

2000-11-14 09:27  miller

	* conf.h: Added new dip.conf variable. Plus allowed dip.conf path
	to be passed in as a parameter

2000-11-14 09:27  miller

	* po_init.c: Added blockage handling (where a wing unit doesn't
	caputure a SC but blockades it, rendering it unbuildable for both
	parties)

2000-11-14 09:27  miller

	* ml_list.c: Various changes including:  - Adjust display for blind
	games  - Display Late Count if enabled	- Display to master who is
	whatching press  - Show new flags  - Different message if game has
	quota but has XF_MANUALSTART set

2000-11-14 09:27  miller

	* bgreet.c: Make Linux compatible

2000-11-14 09:27  miller

	* variant.h: Specify for each variant if it is a homeCentre,
	OneCentre or AnyCentre game.  This makes it clearer for the player
	(who will see this always in a game listing) as well as removing
	specific tests in the code. Plus now any variant uses this only as
	a default - a game setup can change this if required/wanted.

2000-11-14 09:27  miller

	* bailout.c: Small change to log bailout error before bailing out

2000-11-14 09:27  miller

	* summary.c: Accept -C option to specify config_dir Handle blind
	summaries differently (if not master)

